<br>
 He has only dueled once and that was against his best friend Mixxi Bixiebane, who was being swayed to serve Zek.  He dueled her to defend the guards of the Vale whom she had come to see as weak.  When she killed him and saw his blood spilling on the ground, she realized how misguided she had been.  She was punished by the leaders of the Vale, sworn to protect Tuppen, and forced to disarm whenever she entered the Vale from that moment onward.<br>
<br>
For some reason, the thought of dueling with Tuppen (my character) makes me feel as if it would diminish the most significant (and one of the best RP moment) event  with one of his (and my) friends in EQ.  Mixxi's player is gone from EQ now while Mixxi the character is retired.  Preserving Tuppen's only dueling experience by NOT dueling somehow honor's that memory for me, the player, and for Tuppen the character.<br>
<br>
That being said, I love to duel with my secondary character, Ceniwen.  Ceniwen has won about half of the battles she has engaged in and has had some incredible dueling experiences.  As a player, I always find it exhilarating when engaged in a duel...it gets the adrenaline flowing.<br>
<br>
The other day, in Neriak, as Tuppen was aiding one of his favorite paladins in killing tier'dal guards he was taunted and he responded in kind.  When I was approached about a possible duel during /tells, I explianed Tuppen's refusal to duel.  I was quite grateful that the challenger understood the situation.  I feel that I made a RP contact with the folks I chatted with via /tells, while verbally sparing with them in /say.<br>
<br>
Sometimes people have good reasons (and sometimes RP reasons) for refusing to duel.  Please don't sell them short just because they refuse to do so.<br>
<br>
BTW, I did offer to wake up Ceniwen for the challenge despite the fact that the challenger would have been red to her.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   We decided against doing that though. /sigh. <p><img src=http://webpages.marshall.edu/~parsons6/sig.gif>
