<br>
I've also sparred against 3 people at once, 2 of which were even and yellow to me.  And I won, although a 4th person who was 10 levels higher than me gravity fluxed me up and out of the bazaar arena before I could finish off the 3rd person.<br>
<br>
I think some of my favorite dueling experiences have been watching my guild leader and Kazanti go at it.  They're the most entertaining for single one on one duels.  But we've also met battle in the Rathe arena in full force a few times.  It was spectacular.  About 50 people total in one battle, what with all their SK and Necro pets.  We lost in the end, but not after putting up a good fight being very outleveled for the most part.  And silly me I looted my whole corpse before checking and seeing that pain and suffering had killed me and I lost XP.<br>
<br>
Dueling is one of the most fun aspects to role playing.  If you find good roleplayers you'll find people willing to duel.  It's only people who are concerned with their XP bars and not their character who will run from duels.  Besides of course cases like Tuppen's but then he would most likely RP his excuse rather than shouting insults and running, or worse yet, training guards. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.eqfaces.com/photos2/blinkun_copy1.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
