Ven has been under lock and key by a Dark Elf Shadow Knight. Day before he told her to go to the arena. She did as told, and went. There he made her fight his mate. She ran from her the first time when the Rogue was almost dead. She wanted another go so the two ladies went again. She started to run at the end... but this time Ven was quicker and expected her to run. The Rogue died. As taught by her Master, Ven then went and collected a vial of the Rogue's blood. <br>
<br>
After a bit, confident he would win, the Shadow Knight told Ven she would duel him for the blood. Months back Ven dueled her master in practice and he took her blood easily slaying her. He now offered it back to her in exchange for his mates blood. If he won, He would be returned her blood and still keep Ven's. And if Ven won... Well, she would get another vial of blood. Ven said no, knowing she couldn't kill him. Immediately her loyalty was questioned.. so reluctantly she agreed. After a couple of shaky starts they finally began to engage. Ven won. She collected her prize. <br>
<br>
He demanded the blood back, said it was stolen. When Ven explained why she felt it was hers, he in short disowned her... cast her off..<br>
<br>
and ooc... put me on ignore, because he says I played out of character. It makes me sad that he would do something like that because I played Ven totally in character the whole way through it. Instead of rping with me more to get the blood back... I'm on ignore now.. oh well, his loss as I see it. I just don't get it though.<br>
<br>
And to the quote I made at the beginning of this post.. I whole heartily agree. This duel meant allot to me. I expected to die, but I won, against someone I thought was unbeatable by myself.<br>
<br>
Well fought unnamed SK...<br>
<br>
Ven<br>
