<br>
I think it is important to interact a little bit OOC before and after the duel...to make sure both parties know what is happening and what the reason for the duel is.  When someone is decent in an OOC manner, getting your butt kicked is no big deal *chuckles*<br>
<br>
I have lost many duels, won a few...killed those I have lost to after my dead body hits the ground.  And some of my better EQ friends are people I have dueled.<br>
<br>
I do not usually give the challenge when I duel as I am not out looking for a fight...but I respect anyone's right to not duel.  Just don't start the names and trash talk without being willing to at least RP some vengeance play.<br>
